<p>I'm using Symfony Validators to validate user name and password on a form.</p>  <pre><code>$this-&gt;setValidators(array(   'username' =&gt; new sfValidatorEmail(),   'password' =&gt; new sfValidatorString() )); </code></pre>  <p>I'd like to <strong>suppress</strong> the <code>sfValidatorEmail</code>'s error message.  Its default error message is <code>Invalid.</code></p>  <p>I have tried:</p>  <pre><code>$this-&gt;setValidators(array(   'username' =&gt; new sfValidatorEmail(Array(), array('invalid'=&gt;'')),   'password' =&gt; new sfValidatorString() )); </code></pre>  <p>And also,</p>  <pre><code>$this-&gt;setValidators(array(   'username' =&gt; new sfValidatorEmail(Array(), array('invalid'=&gt;NULL)),   'password' =&gt; new sfValidatorString() )); </code></pre>  <p>But neither seems to work.</p>  <p>Is this possible?  And if so, how can I do it?</p>  <p>Thanks</p>